Esma Redžepova (Macedonian: Есма Реџепова) is a Romani Macedonian vocalist, songwriter, and humanitarian born in Skopje, Socialist Republic of Macedonia, then Yugoslavia.
Esma was born on August 8, 1943, in the predominately Romani Šuto Orizari municipality of Skopje, now capital of the FYROM. She is the second youngest of six children.
The movie Gypsy Caravan (2007) features Esma as one of five Romani music acts on their tour through the USA.
